// Phase B-7 — French Top Range Repair sub-service.
// Specialty trade — fewer LA shops handle = strongest practitioner moat.
// Solid steel plate cooking surface, multiple underneath burners providing radiant heat zones.
// $120 commercial diagnostic. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 #1346255700410, .
// Em-dash budget: visible body ≤2.

import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CommercialHero from '../../../components/CommercialHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/commercial/range-repair/french-top-range-repair/";

const title = "French Top Range Repair LA | Solid Plate Cooking Surface, Vulcan, Wolf, Garland";
const description = "Commercial French top range repair across LA, OC, Ventura. Solid steel plate specialty. Vulcan, Jade, Bonnet, Lacanche. BHGS #A49573. $120 dx.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What is a French top range and how is it different from a regular gas range?",
    a: "French top equals a solid steel plate cooking surface instead of open burners. Heat radiates from a center hot spot outward toward cooler edges. The chef positions pots based on temperature needed, closer to the center for higher heat, toward the edges for simmer. This gives one continuous cooking surface with infinite temperature gradient, distinct from open-burner ranges where each burner is a discrete heat zone. Common in French restaurants, classical kitchens, premium European cuisine, and hotel kitchens with French-trained chefs."
  },
  {
    q: "Why do most LA appliance shops decline French top work?",
    a: "Specialty trade. Fewer trained techs in LA because the French top install base is small relative to gas ranges with open burners. Most shops decline because the volume doesn't justify investment in French-top-specific training. Multi-burner diagnostic complexity (4 to 6 underneath burners providing radiant heat zones) requires understanding heat-distribution patterns specific to French top architecture. We service French top routinely; the niche fits our practitioner model. Beverly Hills and West Hollywood premium-French-restaurant base provides steady volume."
  },
  {
    q: "My French top has uneven hot spots. What's the issue?",
    a: "Multi-burner heat distribution issue. The French top relies on 4 to 6 underneath burners producing radiant heat zones across the steel plate. When one or two underneath burners produce uneven output (igniter weak, partial gas flow, thermocouple drift), the plate heat distribution goes off. Diagnostic order: visual inspection from below, individual igniter and thermocouple test on each underneath burner, gas pressure test at the manifold, plate flatness check (warping creates apparent uneven heat). Most cases trace to one or two underneath burner issues."
  },
  {
    q: "My French top plate is warped. Can it be repaired or does it need replacement?",
    a: "Warped plates require specialty fabrication. Year 8 to 12 typical thermal stress causes the steel plate to warp at the center (where heat concentration is highest). Refurbishing isn't field-serviceable, the work requires industrial machining and re-flattening. We coordinate with specialty fabricators for plate work; we don't do plate fabrication directly. Plate replacement runs $1,800 to $3,500+ depending on size (36\", 48\", 60\") and brand. Worth coordinating because a French top range chassis costs $20,000 to $40,000 new and the chassis itself often has 10+ years of life remaining when the plate warps."
  },
  {
    q: "How many underneath burners does a French top have?",
    a: "Depends on plate size. 36\" French top typically has 4 underneath burners. 48\" has 4 to 5. 60\" has 5 to 6. Each underneath burner has its own igniter and thermocouple. Multi-burner diagnostic is the practical reality of French top service; we test each burner individually because failures cluster (one burner igniter failure often paired with adjacent burner thermocouple drift)."
  },
  {
    q: "Vulcan VR-FT vs Wolf Challenger XL FT, which is more reliable?",
    a: "Both are excellent. Vulcan VR-FT (ITW Food Equipment Group) has the broader LA install base and the most accessible parts pipeline through ITW distribution. Wolf Challenger XL FT (Wolf Industrial / Sub-Zero Group commercial division, distinct from residential Wolf) has slightly heavier-duty stainless construction and is favored by chefs who want the marginal increment in plate thermal mass. Both run reliably through year 12 to 15 with proper underneath-burner maintenance. Garland Master FT (Welbilt) and Montague Legend FT (Welbilt) round out the LA premium French top market."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor warranty on every repair. Component manufacturer warranties (Vulcan, Wolf Industrial, Garland, Montague) processed separately through the manufacturer's authorized network. Specialty fabrication for plate work coordinated through external specialty fabricators with their own warranty terms. BHGS #A49573. EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410).  scope. BBB A+ accredited."
  }
];

