<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · French top range service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">French top equals solid steel plate cooking surface. Specialty trade, fewer LA shops handle.</h2>

    <p>French top is the specialty cooking surface of classical European cuisine. <strong>Solid steel plate</strong> instead of open burners. Heat radiates from a center hot spot outward toward cooler edges, the chef positions pots based on temperature needed (closer to center for higher heat, toward edges for simmer). One continuous cooking surface with infinite temperature gradient. Distinct from open-burner ranges where each burner is a discrete heat zone.</p>

    <p>The dominant brands: <strong>Vulcan VR-FT 36/48</strong> (ITW Food Equipment Group), <strong>Wolf Challenger XL FT 48</strong> (Wolf Industrial / Sub-Zero Group commercial division, distinct from residential Wolf), <strong>Garland Master FT 36</strong> (Welbilt), <strong>Montague Legend FT 36</strong> (Welbilt). LA usage concentrates in French restaurants (Beverly Hills, Hollywood), high-end European cuisine, classical kitchens, hotel kitchens with French-trained chefs, and West Hollywood premium operations.</p>

    <p>French top is a specialty trade in LA. Most appliance repair shops decline because the volume doesn't justify investment in French-top-specific training. Multi-burner diagnostic complexity (4 to 6 underneath burners providing radiant heat zones) requires understanding heat-distribution patterns specific to French top architecture. We service French top routinely; the niche fits our practitioner model.</p>

    <p>Plate warping (year 8 to 12 typical thermal stress) requires specialty fabrication. We coordinate with specialty fabricators for plate work; we don't do plate fabrication directly. Plate replacement runs $1,800 to $3,500+ depending on size and brand, but the chassis itself often has 10+ years of life remaining when the plate warps.</p>

    <p><strong>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair.</strong> BHGS #A49573. EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410).  scope. BBB A+ accredited.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 FRENCH TOP FAILURES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · French top specific failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Failure modes distinct from open-burner ranges.</h2>

    <ol class="failure-list">
      <li><strong>Underneath burner system.</strong> 4 to 6 underneath burners providing radiant heat to the plate. Failures: igniter wear (year 4 to 7), thermocouple wear (year 5 to 8), partial gas flow on individual burners. Multi-burner diagnostic required because failures cluster (one burner failure often paired with an adjacent burner issue). $260 to $440 per burner igniter, $220 to $340 per thermocouple.</li>
      <li><strong>Plate warping (year 8 to 12).</strong> Continuous high-heat thermal stress causes the steel plate to warp at the center (where heat concentration is highest). Specialty fabrication required for re-flattening or replacement. We coordinate with specialty fabricators. Plate replacement runs $1,800 to $3,500+.</li>
      <li><strong>Igniter system (multiple igniters underneath).</strong> Each underneath burner has its own igniter. Year 4 to 7 typical wear window per igniter, but on heavy-volume French restaurants we replace as paired sets when adjacent burners are within 6 months of failure window.</li>
      <li><strong>Thermocouples (multiple, one per underneath burner).</strong> Same wear pattern as igniters. Often replaced as paired set with the adjacent igniter.</li>
      <li><strong>Pilot lights (older models).</strong> Pre-electronic-ignition French tops with standing pilots underneath. Pilot orifice clogged or thermocouple weak. $260 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Heat distribution issues.</strong> Uneven burner output across the underneath burners creates uneven plate temps. Diagnostic order: individual burner test, gas pressure test at the manifold, plate flatness check.</li>
      <li><strong>Gas valve degradation (year 8+).</strong> Main gas control valve serving the underneath burner manifold. Less common but creates pressure inconsistencies across all burners simultaneously. $580 to $980.</li>
      <li><strong>Plate cleaning and seasoning.</strong> Steel plate requires regular seasoning maintenance similar to a cast iron skillet but at much larger scale. Restaurant staff handle most plate maintenance; we provide specialty cleaning service when buildup affects heat transfer.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Recent French top repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Four French top jobs from the past 90 days. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly in the LA premium French restaurant market.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>French restaurant in Beverly Hills · Vulcan VR-FT 36\", 6 years old</h3>
        <p>Plate had cool zone at front-left during dinner service prep. Diagnosed: two underneath igniters worn (year 6 underneath igniter wear) plus thermocouple weak on the front-left burner. Replaced two igniters and one thermocouple. Tested heat distribution across plate after restart, recovered to spec gradient. Total: $120 + $360 igniters + $160 thermocouple = $640. Chef noted improvement on first dinner service after repair.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hollywood European restaurant · Wolf Challenger XL FT 48\", 8 years old</h3>
        <p>Multi-burner heat distribution diagnostic plus three underneath igniters. Diagnosed: three igniters at end-of-life (year 8 typical, replaced as paired set with adjacent igniters within 6-month window). Wolf Industrial parts ordered through commercial authorized network (different parts catalog from residential Wolf). Total: $120 + $720 igniters + $140 labor = $980.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hotel kitchen in Beverly Hills · Garland Master FT 36\", 12 years old</h3>
        <p>Plate warping at center plus front-right igniter end-of-life. Plate work coordinated with specialty fabricator (re-flattening service, 5-day turnaround off-site). Replaced front-right igniter while plate was off. Total: $120 + $1,800 plate fabrication coordination + $260 igniter + $220 labor = $2,400. Chassis itself has 5+ more years of service life with refurbished plate.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Premium restaurant in West Hollywood · Montague Legend FT 36\", 7 years old</h3>
        <p>Multi-burner cleaning (heavy carbon buildup on underneath burner ports) plus two thermocouples weak. Deep-cleaned all 4 underneath burners, replaced two thermocouples. Tested heat distribution after restart. Total: $120 + $440 thermocouples + $160 burner cleaning = $720. Set restaurant on quarterly maintenance contract going forward.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we service, what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong> Vulcan VR-FT 36/48, Wolf Challenger XL FT 48 (Wolf Industrial commercial), Garland Master FT 36, Montague Legend FT 36, and other French top range configurations. Underneath burner igniter and thermocouple service (multi-burner diagnostic), pilot system service on older models, gas valve replacement, multi-burner heat distribution diagnostic, plate cleaning and seasoning service, plate warping coordination with specialty fabricators.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>Plate fabrication or re-flattening (specialty industrial trade); we coordinate with specialty fabricators when plate work is needed</li>
      <li>New French top installation (specialty installer trade with gas line and ventilation work)</li>
      <li>Plate seasoning as standalone service (restaurant staff scope; we provide it as part of cleaning service when accumulated buildup affects heat transfer)</li>
      <li>Type I exhaust hood work above the range (see <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/">exhaust hood repair</a>)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 PRICING -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">French top range repair costs in Southern California.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Diagnostic is $120 (commercial tier), waived with repair. Written estimate before any repair work begins.</p>

    <table class="price-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Repair</th><th>Cost</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Diagnostic</td><td>$120, waived with repair</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Underneath burner igniter (per burner)</td><td>$260 to $440</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Thermocouple (per burner)</td><td>$220 to $340</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-burner heat distribution diagnostic plus paired-set igniter replacement</td><td>$640 to $1,200</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Pilot system service (older models, per pilot)</td><td>$260 to $440</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Gas valve replacement</td><td>$580 to $980</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Plate cleaning and seasoning service</td><td>$280 to $440</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Plate warping fabrication coordination (re-flatten vs replacement, specialty external)</td><td>$1,800 to $3,500+</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Quarterly maintenance contract (per visit)</td><td>$320 to $480</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-component repair</td><td>$900 to $1,800</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty</td><td>90 days parts plus labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 BRANDS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · Brands</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">French top range brands we service.</h2>

    <ul class="brand-list">
      <li><strong>Vulcan</strong> (ITW Food Equipment Group). VR-FT 36 and VR-FT 48. Broadest LA install base for French top. <a href="/brands/vulcan-range-repair/">Vulcan range repair brand page</a> and <a href="/brands/vulcan/">Vulcan brand hub</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Wolf Industrial</strong> (Sub-Zero Group commercial division). Challenger XL FT 48. Distinct parts catalog from residential Wolf cooking. Heavier-duty stainless construction. <a href="/brands/wolf-range-repair/">Wolf range repair brand page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Garland</strong> (Welbilt). Master FT 36. Common in mid-volume French restaurant operations. <a href="/brands/garland-range-repair/">Garland range repair brand page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Montague</strong> (Welbilt). Legend FT 36. Premium tier. <a href="/brands/montague-oven-repair/">Montague oven repair brand page</a> (range service available through same dispatch).</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 07 WHY US -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">07 · Why operators call us</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Eight reasons.</h2>

    <ul class="why-list">
      <li><strong>French top specialty.</strong> Most LA appliance shops decline French top work; the niche fits our practitioner model.</li>
      <li><strong>Multi-burner diagnostic expertise.</strong> 4 to 6 underneath burners providing radiant heat zones. We test individually and identify cluster failures before they cascade.</li>
      <li><strong>Plate fabrication coordination.</strong> Specialty fabricator referral relationship for plate warping work. Honest scope: we don't do plate fabrication ourselves but we coordinate.</li>
      <li><strong>Wolf Commercial vs residential disambiguation.</strong> Different parts catalogs, different authorized service networks. We verify by serial number and source through the correct pipeline.</li>
      <li><strong>Quarterly maintenance contracts.</strong> Predictable maintenance budget for premium French restaurants. High-volume kitchens benefit most.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS #A49573 plus EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410) scope.</strong> See our <a href="/credentials/licensed/">licensing page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>$120 commercial diagnostic, no after-hours surcharge.</strong> Phones answered 24/7.</li>
      <li><strong>Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura.</strong> Beverly Hills, Hollywood, West Hollywood premium-French-restaurant base served from multiple branches.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Sister sub-services: <a href="/commercial/range-repair/gas-range-repair/">commercial gas range repair</a>, <a href="/commercial/range-repair/restaurant-range-salamander-repair/">restaurant range with salamander broiler</a>. Sister pillars: <a href="/commercial/oven-repair/">commercial oven repair</a>, <a href="/commercial/grill-repair/">commercial grill repair</a>, <a href="/commercial/griddle-repair/">commercial griddle repair</a>, <a href="/commercial/charbroiler-repair/">commercial charbroiler repair</a>, <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/">commercial exhaust hood repair</a>. Parent: <a href="/commercial/range-repair/">commercial range repair pillar</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 08 FAQ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">08 · FAQ</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">French top range repair, common questions.</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map(f => (
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>{f.q}</summary>
